  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was a nice Jew, the same thing like he was-- like he would have been before.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what he could, he did for people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One day, we heard rumors that we are are going to get taken-- they are going to take us to the Ukraine in the battle line to work alongside there on the front.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "To carry ammunition, dig trenches and bunkers, and so on, and so on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was the truth.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Horrible, horrible.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The working conditions-- they were very bad, but the-- the beatings were even worse.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For every little thing, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they tied you up [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to the back, with your hands and a rope, they tied it up to the-- tied up your feet.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then they pulled up the rope, and you were on the point of your finger-- toes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that high, they pulled you up, that a newspaper, they could have [? pulled ?] through to your feet, because it means you had to [? lift ?] only on your nerves.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that would be, you know, for two hours, depends for how long you were sentenced.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If you-- if you-- if you fainted, they took a pail of cold water, they throw it over you, and back up again.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The sentence had to be carried out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] They took us to the battle line.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And here, I'm talking-- you know, it is easier said than done.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because we were Jews, we weren't so much in the necessity, you know, to go to the battle line, than the soldiers, the fighting soldiers.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the train with the soldiers-- they had to let them go through.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they [INAUDIBLE] deadline until everything [INAUDIBLE] during the night.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
